    <item>
      <title>Some news</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=11277#M11277</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;You may have noticed that the top 10 issues list hasn't been updated for quite some time, and also that some of these issues have not been addressed for an even longer time. Since this list started, many changes were made to the game, and slowly it has accumulated dead issues. They are tagged as &amp;quot;currently being discussed&amp;quot; or &amp;quot;currently being evaluated&amp;quot;, but the reality is that devs seem to have relied less and less on class lists, to the point that maintaining them is no longer efficient.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;It seems to me that devs are getting feedback from other sources, and have stopped using these lists altogether. In their current incarnation, they have outlived their purpose.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I believe, however, that keeping a record of issues we have, and how we would like the game to change for us in the future, still makes sense. I also believe that restricting it to only 10 items is good and helps getting to the point.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;So I have decided to cleanup and reorganize the list a little bit, which means eliminating some items and adding a couple others from &lt;a target="_blank" href="http://www.eqcleric.com/forums/showthread.php?s=&amp;threadid=10733"&gt;this thread&lt;/a&gt;. It also means that from now on we shouldn't expect to see any dev input about this list, although I hope the see the fixes coming, and to see the game move in the general direction it describes. Expect to see Kytherea post the new list soon.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Now for the news. I have been given (as well as other correspondents) the opportunity to ask questions to the devs with a real chance of obtaining answers. Of course it's a limited &amp;quot;offer&amp;quot;, and I intend to be very careful not to abuse it. It's pretty successful so far, unfortunately the proximity of E3 and the fact that Oshran (the dev in charge of AA) is too busy learning the system to answer have delayed the responses to cleric questions.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Nevertheless, expect to see me post new Q&amp;amp;A from time to time.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;You are free to post your own questions anywhere on this board of course, but for once I reserve the right to select those I find pertinent, or just mine if I see fit. The reason for this is that most questions are already answered if you do a search, but also because I expect them to take the form &amp;quot;can we have this and that?&amp;quot; which is in my opinion just a devious way to post a wishlist.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
