    <item>
      <title>Suggestions for discussion</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=11235#M11235</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;It's nice to see that there are other clerics out there who are not fully satisfied with how our class is being managed.  It seems anytime I post a suggestion for cleric change someone (usually not a cleric) feels the urge to tell me how wrong I am and insult me in the bargain.  We get complete heal .. how dare we ask for anything else?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Some would relegate us to healer/rezzer/buffer alone.  I don't mind being &amp;quot;just&amp;quot; the healer most of the time but I do find it annoying that we don't get better cure abilities.  I'd also like to see broad spectrum resist spells. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If we can return a person from the dead isn't it logical to think that we could cure any disease/ poison/ curse without a ridiculously long recast/ AA reuse timer? Wouldn't it make sense to let us cast a group cure more than every 2.5 minutest? Many mobs recast their detrimental spells almost immediately after they are cured. Why should I have to wait to be able to counteract those detrimental affects? &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We do get word of divination and I love it but why give us a group heal with cures built in but not give us a group cure without the heal built in for a more reasonable mana cost? Why should I have to use so much of my mana to cure my group when they don't need the heal portion?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I would add that a buff that raises resists across the board by at least 100. Currently only bards get that ability and it's far better than anything any other class can manage.  (not including vet rewards)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Lastly, I would add a focus affect that improves our cures ( much like bards get improvements to their instruments that in turn improves their cures). &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Respectfully&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
