      <title>Cleric Aura's (Level 70 is a waste of time)</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=11055#M11055</link>
      <description>After a bit of work I managed to get my lvl 55 and lvl 70 auras for my Cleric. I wanted to verify the working of the lvl 70 aura verus the lvl 55 aura.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Now granted a lvl 55 may not be as quick as me to get the lvl 55, but I still do not see the value of the lvl 70 aura. I do like the aura but I would only recommend that a cleric bother with the lvl 55 version as it stands.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Lvl 55 aura&lt;br&gt;Mana: 416&lt;br&gt;Cast time: 6 seconds.&lt;br&gt;Effect: 5% melee damage reduction max 300 points&lt;br&gt;Time to aquire: 30mins.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Lvl 70 aura&lt;br&gt;Mana: 500&lt;br&gt;Cast time: 3 seconds.&lt;br&gt;Effect: 5% melee damage reduction max 300 points&lt;br&gt;Time to aquire: 8 hours (3 group missions with no worth wild loot) Ohh and one boss mob has a nice 8k DD time delay nuke.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;(The effects does not stack with the Vie line.)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;An example of a good aura. Monk lvl is 55 5% to dodge, ripost, and parry. Monk lvl 70 is 10% to dodge, ripost, and parry.</description>
