    <item>
      <title>unique and religious</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=10949#M10949</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We want something unique we want something religion based.  I think I have an idea.  It is one that is &amp;quot;stolen&amp;quot; from D&amp;amp;D 3rd edition: &amp;quot;domains&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In D&amp;amp;D 3rd edition &amp;quot;domains&amp;quot; are additional powers and spells granted by the cleric's god.  Each god has three to five domains which it &amp;quot;controls&amp;quot; and a cleric of that god chooses two of these domains.   Each domain comes with a special granted power.  Some granted powers are simply a boost in power with certain spell types (cleric casts these spells at one level higher than he is), some are abilities that a cleric would not normally have (the ability to use a weapon not normally usable by a cleric), and some are abilities that can only be used once per day (the ability to provide a party member with additional protection [improves saves]).  In addition to granted powers, each domain provides an additional spell at each level, the cleric has to choose which of his two spells per level to memorize though.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I think this system could be adapted to EQ.  I would think that additional spells would be out of the question since in EQ no memorization is required, but the &amp;quot;granted powers&amp;quot; piece would be  unique to the cleric class and be religious in nature since it is the god granting the cleric that power.  Now by no means would these powers be overwhelming and unbalancing.  Some of the D&amp;amp;D ones are:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Air, fire, earth and water domains grant the cleric the ability to turn the respective type creature as they would an undead creature.  In EQ terms an Air domain cleric could use his Turn undead AA against Air elemental mobs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Healing domain grants a +1 cast level boost to all healing spells.  In EQ terms a small percentage healing boost that stacks with other foci.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strength domain grants the ability to perform a feat of strength once per day.  in eq terms a short duration extreme strength bonus.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;War domain grants the cleric the ability to use a weapon type specific to the god he worships even if that weapon is not normally available in his repitiore and gets a bonus to hit and atk when using a weapon of that type.  In EQ terms, like the druid having access to scimitar weapons, a cleric of a specific god could have access to a specific 1hs weapon (i.e a dwarf can weild a battle axe).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Trickery domain grants the cleric Bluff disguise and hide as class skills.  In EQ terms, the cleric in question would be granted the hide and sneak skill though limited to a reasonable cap.  (this one may be too powerful as invis is the one thing all clerics want :smileywink: ).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;What I would do, is establish a quest/mission NPC in each home temple that would detail each granted power of the god in question (remember each god has limited access to what powers it can grant), so that each player can make an informed decision as to what he/she wants.  Once the decision is made, the cleric then goes on a series of quests.  At first, the rewards are items with click or focus effects that provide the granted power.  Initial quests are simple so that any level 20 (fassume these quests start after the tutorial) and up can do them, but the rewards are equally &amp;quot;simple&amp;quot;.  As the cleric completes quests/missions the items steadily improve.  Eventually however, items normally acquired in the game will out perform those granted through this quest series.  So, at some point (probablly around level 51) the quests change from rewarding items to rewarding AAs providing passive improvements or clickable abilities.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;What do you think?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Fri, 24 Mar 2006 08:05:46 GMT</pubDate>
      <author>Thaere</author>
      <guid>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=10949#M10949</guid>
      <dc:creator>Thaere</dc:creator>
      <dc:date>2006-03-24T08:05:46Z</dc:date>
    </item>
