      <title>Cleric Issue List</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=10902#M10902</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;3. Please evaluate the defensive skills and abilities of clerics. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;knight will have varying results on actual damage taken (not hit rate, which is controlled by secondary skills, but actual damage per hit) It is our belief that clerics have enough real penalties due to lack of secondary skills (riposte, parry, AA), that also having soft caps and tables that lead to different results with the same skills is excessive and detrimental.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color="#66cc00"&gt;Was this not handled already?  A short time ago, the developers announced that they were &amp;quot;correcting&amp;quot; this problem by changed the Cleric AC table to mimic bards instead of casters.  Is #3 different or the same?&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="timetext1"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;7. Add more lore and quests related to religion &lt;font color="#339999"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(NEW)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;At lower level clerics can see how their chosen race and religion impact their EQ life.  They can complte specific quests (symbol), and must take faction into account.  As they level up, religion no longer make any difference.  We would like to see religion matter again in the game, with new deity-specific quests and items for instance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="timetext1"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color="#66cc00"&gt;Thank goodness something new.  The Invis issue is off the list.  Some are not going to be very happy about it, but I personally feel (as I have said many times) Sony has done enough and has made regular invisibility very accessible to clerics (and other non-invis spell classes).  The solution may not be popular, but it is usable and balanced.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;</description>
